OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAntique rifle thief gets a 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fday in jail decades on from
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fhis museum heists          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, After a crime spree spanning decades,  
OL,6, antique thief Thomas Gavin had just one
OL,7, explanation for his museum heists: he  
OL,8, likes "collecting" old things.         
OL,10,FMr Gavin, 78, has now been sentenced to
OL,11,Fone day in jail after being caught     
OL,12,Ftrying to sell a rare rifle dating back
OL,13,Fto the US Revolutionary War.           
OL,15,FWhen questioned, he admitted to dozens 
OL,16,Fof other robberies in the 1960s and    
OL,17,F1970s and apologised for the trouble.  
OL,19,FProsecutors on Tuesday said "justice   
OL,20,Ffinally caught up", four decades later.
